HEADWORD: Myochrome
<hw>My"o*chrome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Myo-</ets> +
Gr. <?/ color.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A colored albuminous
substance in the serum from red-colored muscles. It is identical with
hemoglobin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

